               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-89-person632">
                  JAMES 
                  LILES
               <interp inst="t18280110-89-person632" type="surname" value="LILES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-89-person632" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-89-person632" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a bricklayer. On the 10th of December I was sitting at Townsend's window; a woman gave me information - I ran out, and saw the prisoner and another running, about five yards off; I overtook the prisoner, and threw him down - the other, who got away, threw this piece of cheese to the prisoner; it fell between his hands into the kennel, and I took it up.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-89-person633">
                  SARAH 
                  TOWNSEND
               <interp inst="t18280110-89-person633" type="surname" value="TOWNSEND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-89-person633" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-89-person633" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of Jacob Townsend - we <rs id="t18280110-89-viclabel447" type="occupation">keep a chandler's-shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-89-victim631 t18280110-89-viclabel447"></join> in <placeName id="t18280110-89-crimeloc448">John's-row, Waterloo-street, St. Luke's.</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-89-crimeloc448" type="placeName" value="John's-row, Waterloo-street, St. Luke's."></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-89-crimeloc448" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-89-off445 t18280110-89-crimeloc448"></join> About ten minutes past nine o'clock in the evening, I was in the parlour, and saw a man run out with the cheese; I told Liles, and followed him out: I saw the cheese in the kennel - I know it by having cut a piece off this corner.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182801100065"></xptr>
            
